#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np18"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Kosiyavagga"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "18. Rūpiyasikkhāpada"
msgstr "18. The training rule on money"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.237"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.18.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.99"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2203"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto aññatarassa kulassa "
"kulūpako hoti niccabhattiko."
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Upananda was associating with a family from which he "
"received a regular meal."

#. VAR: paṭiviso → paṭiviṃso (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ tasmiṃ kule uppajjati khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā tato āyasmato "
"upanandassa sakyaputtassa paṭiviso ṭhapiyyati."
msgstr ""
"Whenever that family obtained food, they put aside a portion for Upananda."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sāyaṃ tasmiṃ kule maṃsaṃ uppannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "And that’s what they did when one evening they obtained some meat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Tato āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa paṭiviso ṭhapito hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Tassa kulassa dārako rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya rodati—"
msgstr "The following morning one of their children got up and cried,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“maṃsaṃ me dethā”ti."
msgstr "“Give me meat!”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "The man said to his wife,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“ayyassa paṭivisaṃ dārakassa dehi."
msgstr "“Give the Venerable’s portion to the child."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Aññaṃ cetāpetvā ayyassa dassāmā”ti."
msgstr "We’ll buy something else for the Venerable.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2204"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaraṃ "
"ādāya yena taṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"On the same morning, Upananda robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to "
"that family,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on the prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The man of the house approached Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.14"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“hiyyo kho, bhante, sāyaṃ maṃsaṃ uppannaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "“Yesterday evening, Venerable, we obtained some meat,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Tato ayyassa paṭiviso ṭhapito."
msgstr "and we put aside a portion for you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhante, dārako rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya rodati—"
msgstr "But then in the morning our child got up and cried,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "‘maṃsaṃ me dethā’ti."
msgstr "‘Give me meat!’,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.100"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Ayyassa paṭiviso dārakassa dinno."
msgstr "and we gave your portion to the child."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "Kahāpaṇena, bhante, kiṃ āhariyyatū”ti?"
msgstr "What can we get you for the sum of a <i lang=\"pli\">kahāpaṇa</i>?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "“Pariccatto me, āvuso, kahāpaṇo”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you giving up a <i lang=\"pli\">kahāpaṇa</i> coin for me?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "“Āma, bhante, pariccatto”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, Venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "“Taññeva me, āvuso, kahāpaṇaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Then just give me that <i lang=\"pli\">kahāpaṇa</i>.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2205"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.25"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so puriso āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa kahāpaṇaṃ datvā "
"ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr ""
"After giving a <i lang=\"pli\">kahāpaṇa</i> to Upananda, that man grumbled "
"and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.26"
msgid ""
"“Yatheva mayaṃ rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā rūpiyaṃ "
"paṭiggaṇhantī”ti."
msgstr "“Just as we accept money, so do the Sakyan ascetics.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.101"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda receive money?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2206"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.31"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena "
"vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

#. VAR: paṭiggahesī”ti → paṭiggaṇhāsīti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.32"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.34"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.35"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahessasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you receive money?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.102"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.36"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.37"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.37a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2207"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.38"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu jātarūparajataṃ uggaṇheyya vā uggaṇhāpeyya vā upanikkhittaṃ "
"vā sādiyeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk takes, gets someone else to take, or consents to gold and silver "
"being deposited for him, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.39"
msgid "(<em>18</em>:<strong>37</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.39a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.238"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.40"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.41"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.42"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.43"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.44"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2209"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.45"
msgid "Jātarūpaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Gold:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.46"
msgid "satthuvaṇṇo vuccati."
msgstr "the color of the Teacher is what is meant."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2210"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.47"
msgid "Rajataṃ nāma"
msgstr "Silver:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.48"
msgid "kahāpaṇo lohamāsako dārumāsako jatumāsako ye vohāraṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"a <i lang=\"pli\">kahāpaṇa</i> coin, a copper <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> "
"coin, a wooden <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coin, a resin <i lang=\"pli\""
">māsaka</i> coin; whatever is used in commerce."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.103"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2211"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.49"
msgid "Uggaṇheyyāti"
msgstr "Takes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyaṃ hoti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.50"
msgid "sayaṃ gaṇhāti nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if he takes it himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2212"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.51"
msgid "Uggaṇhāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets someone else to take:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyaṃ hoti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.52"
msgid "aññaṃ gāhāpeti nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if he gets another to take it, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2213"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.53"
msgid "Upanikkhittaṃ vā sādiyeyyāti"
msgstr "Consents to […] being deposited for him:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.54"
msgid "idaṃ ayyassa hotūti upanikkhittaṃ sādiyati, nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"if someone says, “Let this be for you,” and he consents to it being "
"deposited for him, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.55"
msgid "Saṃghamajjhe nissajjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "It should be relinquished in the midst of the Order."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.56"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ—"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.57"
msgid ""
"tena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa "
"vacanīyo—"
msgstr ""
"After approaching the Order, that monk should put his upper robe over one "
"shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then "
"squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.58"
msgid "“ahaṃ, bhante, rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahesiṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, I have received money."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.59"
msgid "Idaṃ me nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "It is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.60"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.61"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "”After relinquishing it, he is to confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.62"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The confession should be received by a competent and capable monk."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.63"
msgid "Sace tattha āgacchati ārāmiko vā upāsako vā so vattabbo—"
msgstr ""
"If a monastery attendant or a lay follower is available, you should tell him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.64"
msgid "“āvuso, imaṃ jānāhī”ti."
msgstr "“Look into this.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.65"
msgid "Sace so bhaṇati—"
msgstr "If he says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.66"
msgid "“iminā kiṃ āhariyyatū”ti,"
msgstr "“What can I get you with this?”,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.67"
msgid "na vattabbo—"
msgstr "you should not say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.68"
msgid "“imaṃ vā imaṃ vā āharā”ti."
msgstr "“Get this or that;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.69"
msgid "Kappiyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ—"
msgstr "you should point out what is allowable:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.70"
msgid "sappi vā telaṃ vā madhu vā phāṇitaṃ vā."
msgstr "ghee, oil, honey, or sugar."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.71"
msgid ""
"Sace so tena parivattetvā kappiyaṃ āharati rūpiyappaṭiggāhakaṃ ṭhapetvā "
"sabbeheva paribhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he makes a purchase and brings back what is allowable, everyone may enjoy "
"it except the one who received the money."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.72"
msgid "Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If this is what happens, that is good."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.104"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.73"
msgid "no ce labhetha, so vattabbo—"
msgstr "If not, you should tell him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.74"
msgid "“āvuso, imaṃ chaḍḍehī”ti."
msgstr "“Discard this.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.75"
msgid "Sace so chaḍḍeti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he discards it, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.76"
msgid ""
"no ce chaḍḍeti, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu rūpiyachaḍḍako "
"sammannitabbo—"
msgstr ""
"If he does not, a monk who has five qualities should be appointed as the "
"money-discarder:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.77"
msgid ""
"yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, "
"na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, chaḍḍitāchaḍḍitañca jāneyya."
msgstr ""
"one who is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and who "
"understands the meaning of discarded and not discarded."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.78"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo."
msgstr "“And, monks, this is how he should be appointed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.79"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo."
msgstr "First the monk should be asked"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.80"
msgid "Yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2214"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.81"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.82"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ rūpiyachaḍḍakaṃ "
"sammanneyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, it should appoint monk so-and-so as "
"the money-discarder."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.83"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2215"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.84"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.85"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ rūpiyachaḍḍakaṃ sammannati."
msgstr "The Order appoints monk so-and-so as the money-discarder."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.86"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno rūpiyachaḍḍakassa sammuti, so "
"tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who agrees to appointing monk so-and-so as the money-discarder "
"should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.87"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not agree should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2216"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.88"
msgid "Sammato saṃghena itthannāmo bhikkhu rūpiyachaḍḍako."
msgstr "The Order has appointed monk so-and-so as the money-discarder."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.89"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.90"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2217"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.91"
msgid "Tena sammatena bhikkhunā animittaṃ katvā pātetabbaṃ."
msgstr "The appointed monk should drop it without taking note of the location."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.92"
msgid "Sace nimittaṃ katvā pāteti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he takes note of where he drops it, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.92a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.239"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.105"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2218"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.93"
msgid "Rūpiye rūpiyasaññī rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is money, and he perceives it as money, and he receives it, he commits "
"an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.94"
msgid "Rūpiye vematiko rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is money, but he is unsure if it is, and he receives it, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.95"
msgid "Rūpiye arūpiyasaññī rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is money, but he does not perceive it as money, and he receives it, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2219"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.96"
msgid "Arūpiye rūpiyasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not money, but he perceives it as money, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.97"
msgid "Arūpiye vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not money, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.98"
msgid "Arūpiye arūpiyasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not money, and he does not perceive it as money, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.98a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2220"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.99"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.100"
msgid "ajjhārāme vā ajjhāvasathe vā uggahetvā vā uggahāpetvā vā nikkhipati—"
msgstr ""
"if, within a monastery or a house, he takes it or gets someone to take it, "
"and then puts it aside with the thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.101"
msgid "yassa bhavissati so harissatīti,"
msgstr "“Whoever this belongs to will fetch it;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.102"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.103"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2221"></a> 
#. VAR: Rūpiyasikkhāpadaṃ → jāta­rūpa­sikkhā­pada (kaṅkhāvitaraṇī)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:pts-cs1.104"
msgid "Rūpiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on money, is finished."

